      "posted_at": "2026-05-26T08:20:10-0400",
      "body": "NO TRADES - but feel free to throw me reasonable offers! Dave's Guitar Shop Special Edition AVRI Stratocaster There's not another one around, these are very limited runs. I can send you a demo video if you really need to hear what a Strat sounds like... It's an open secret that some of the best guitars go to dealer runs and the Dave's Guitars is one of the pickiest and best Fender dealers there is. These are made for Dave's to Dave's spec - I think these are, for any money, some of the best strats you can get. You have to move up to a much more expensive/Custom Shop guitar to find these specs. If you're unfamiliar, these are a custom run for Dave's Guitar Shop out of Wisconsin with the following specs: Nitro Sonic Blue American Vintage Reissue 1962-style Body and Hardware Custom shop Fat 50s pickups 9.5\" Radius Medium Jumbo frets Besutiful dark red rosewood fretboard Dark Aged Clay fretmarkers Reissue brown tolex case Case candy, strap, ashtray bridge cover, and 75th anniversary bridge plate included Basically a vintage body and electronics with a modern fretboard and radius. Hard to find and limited to one color each year. These are amazing guitars and I'm sure I will be mad at myself for letting it go, but I'm just too much of a baby about it to take it out and gig with it and it has stayed on my wall or in the case. It does have some marks, most notably on the back near the lower horn. There's a little paint chip by the neck pocket edge and various small marks on the body/ pickgaurd. A lot of this is hard to see, you need to be right up close in the right light. It's nothing like a relic job, just some natural wear on a guitar you won't be able to put down.",
